annotationA: Spindle assembly abnormal 4 is a centriole protein that is essential for centriole assembly. It is recruited to centrioles through an interaction with the centriole protein ana2, and it helps recruit microtubules to the centriole
annotationB: Protein stand still; Essential in the female germline for proper survival, sex determination and differentiation. Participates in the transcriptional activation of Otu. Does not regulate the expression of Ovo
